<p>There is also a lower bandwidth two-way communication version of DRM as a replacement for SSB communications on HF <sup id="cite_ref-5" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-5" title=""><span>[</span>6<span>]</span></a></sup>- note that it is NOT compatible with the official DRM specification.</p>
<p>The <a href="/wiki/Dream_DRM_Receiver" title="Dream DRM Receiver">Dream software</a> will receive the commercial versions and also limited transmission mode using the FAAC AAC encoder.</p>
<p><a name="Error_coding" id="Error_coding"></a></p>
<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Digital_Radio_Mondiale&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8" title="Edit section: Error coding">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Error coding</span></h3>
<p>Error coding can be chosen to be more or less robust.</p>
