<p><a name="DRM.27s_COFDM" id="DRM.27s_COFDM"></a></p>
<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Digital_Radio_Mondiale&amp;action=edit&amp;section=17" title="Edit section: DRM's COFDM">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">DRM's COFDM</span></h3>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.ebu.ch/en/technical/trev/trev_278-stott.pdf" class="external text" title="http://www.ebu.ch/en/technical/trev/trev_278-stott.pdf" rel="nofollow">"The how and why of COFDM"</a> Jonathan Stott. <a href="/wiki/European_Broadcasting_Union" title="European Broadcasting Union">EBU</a>: <i><a href="http://www.ebu.ch/en/technical/trev/trev_home.html" class="external text" title="http://www.ebu.ch/en/technical/trev/trev_home.html" rel="nofollow">EBU Technical Review</a></i> 278 (winter 1998).</li>
<li><a href="http://www.bbc.co.uk/rd/pubs/papers/paper_15/paper_15.html" class="external text" title="http://www.bbc.co.uk/rd/pubs/papers/paper_15/paper_15.html" rel="nofollow">Explaining some of the magic of COFDM, J H Stott (BBC)</a>: "<a href="/wiki/COFDM" title="COFDM" class="mw-redirect">COFDM</a> is particularly well matched to these applications, since it is very tolerant of the effects of <a href="/wiki/Multipath" title="Multipath">multipath</a>."</li>
<li><a href="http://www.digitalradiotech.co.uk/cofdm.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.digitalradiotech.co.uk/cofdm.htm" rel="nofollow">Coded Orthogonal Frequency Division Multiplexing (COFDM)</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.sss-mag.com/ofdm.html" class="external text" title="http://www.sss-mag.com/ofdm.html" rel="nofollow">All About OFDM from SSS Online and Pegasus Technologies</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.palowireless.com/ofdm/tutorials.asp" class="external text" title="http://www.palowireless.com/ofdm/tutorials.asp" rel="nofollow">OFDM, VOFDM, COFDM, Orthogonal Frequency Division Multiplexing: tutorials</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.palowireless.com/ofdm/resources.asp" class="external text" title="http://www.palowireless.com/ofdm/resources.asp" rel="nofollow">OFDM, VOFDM, COFDM, Orthogonal Frequency Division Multiplexing: resources</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.digitaltelevision.com/cofdm/" class="external text" title="http://www.digitaltelevision.com/cofdm/" rel="nofollow">COFDM/8-VSB Controversy Archive &amp; Links</a></li>
</ul>
<p><a name="Index" id="Index"></a></p>
